Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Soak your @bamboo skewers{4} in cold water (this will prevent them from burning).

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{some}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve and peel the @red onion{1}, then cut each half into 3 wedges.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @Indonesian style spice mix{1%sachet} with a drizzle of @oil{some} to make your marinade. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Drain the @fish pie mix{1%pack} and pat dry with #kitchen paper{}. Add it to the #bowl{} of marinade along with the onion wedges. Mix well so everything's coated.

Thread the fish and onion onto the skewers (2 per person), alternating between the two. Pop the skewers onto a large baking tray.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

When the chips are about halfway through cooking, turn them over.

At the same time, pop your skewers on the middle shelf of your oven to cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

While everything's in the oven, boil a half-full #kettle{}. Quarter the @lime{1}.

In a medium bowl, combine a good squeeze of lime juice with the @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing (see pantry for both amounts). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the @coleslaw mix{120%g} to the bowl and toss together. Set aside.

A few mins before everything's ready, add the @peanut butter{30%g} and @boiling water{1.5%tbsp} (see pantry for amount) to a #jug{} or #small bowl{}.

Mix together well, then stir in the @sweet chilli sauce{32%g}. Squeeze in some lime juice, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

When everything's ready, share the fish skewers between your plates and drizzle over the satay sauce.

Serve the chips and pickled slaw alongside, along with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!